author: AkiratheWhite
text:
Not sure if you read English comments, but I just had something to say. I don't mean to be pretentious; you were the first VTuber from HoloLive that i found, I always found your videos to be extremely entertaining and enjoyable.

I saw what happened the other day when people were telling you to end your stream, around HoloLive EN's debut. Speaking honestly, I've never seen you so genuinely upset before. It was very hard for me to not feel upset as well.

I hope that you're feeling better now, and that your fans have continued to support you. Please take good care of your physical and mental health, for your own sake and your fans. You've probably worked very hard to get to where you are right now, and I'd like to see you reach even greater heights.

Best wishes,
A random overseas viewer

author: Zamiq Shelton
text: May I ask your learning method? I've been using duolingo but I feel like I'm not learning much.

author: 606hunter1
text:
Zamiq Shelton not sure if that's directed at me but I use a few methods. 
1. Looking up words that I commonly use in English translated to Japanese and then writing them so I can retain better
2. Listening and repeating phrases I hear from hololive, movies, etc.
3. Removing the safety net of subtitles and writing down what I think I hear
4. Learn as much vocabulary as you can cause it's very difficult if you don't recognize words

PSA: depending on your native language it'll take way longer to learn Japanese compared to others so don't lose hope. Use whatever motivates you to stay with it.

author: KaZupoon✖️🎣
text:
配信お疲れ様でした。
動画中でmonikaとして出演していた者です。
初見、途中参加、並びに初のオンライン対戦だったためお部屋のルールに気づけなくてごめんなさい！
もうちょっと周りを見て空気読めてれば……迷惑をおかけしました。
今後はもっと注意します。決して害悪プレイしたかったつもりではないので、視聴者さんもその点ご了承頂きたい…！
また対戦で当たったときはちゃんとルール確認して、すっきり対戦したいです！
本当にお疲れ様でした。
長文失礼しました！
(p.s.)抜けた後、回線の状態がいいのにエラー出てつながらないときがあったんですが、何なんでしょう？
(『通信側からの応答がない』と出る)
BAN...じゃないですよね？
めちゃくちゃ不安です。誰か
わかる人教えてください！
